healing from shame. learning to love and forgive myself for.. 

for all of the times I've covered my body up in sweatsuits and xl tees out of shame. 

for when i convinced myself my shape was offensive bcus I wasn't small or my stomach wasn't flat. 

for believing someone I once really admired when they told me men would only ever like me bcus I had a booty. 

for still not taking my shirt off at the gym 😂 

for how I resented my body for protecting me when I didn't protect her. 

for being afraid to make this a reel and not just leave it on my story 😏

I love love LOVE you girl.

Making curly hair from synthetic braiding hair ✨

Story time: So im headed to my clients house and got this bright idea about a style I wanted to do for her premiere look, but I didn't have the hair I needed to execute the look 🥴 and I'm NO WHERE near a hair store for black women (thanks for nothin, LA 🙄). All I have is regular synthetic braiding hair. So I get to her house and ask if she has anything like a rod or small pole. All she has is 3 old packs of chop sticks lol.. 🤔 ok, let's get it. I got creative and this was the outcome. I love how these curls turned out. Now I want to try other curl patterns. TBC ☺️
details and definition. I love the contrast in @trevornoah curls when im defining the pattern. 😍
